01:31.510 --> 01:32.510
Ow!

01:32.510 --> 01:35.010
Ow, oh, I got a cramp!

01:35.010 --> 01:36.510
What are you
doing, Ralph?

01:36.510 --> 01:38.010
Oh, my leg, my leg's in a knot!

01:38.010 --> 01:39.520
Will you get
your leg down, Ralph?

01:39.520 --> 01:41.520
Oh, rub it, Rich, will you?

01:41.520 --> 01:44.020
I'm not gonna rub your
leg, it's ridiculous.

01:44.020 --> 01:45.140
Wait till you get a cramp.

01:45.140 --> 01:47.220
I can't handle this
necking in a car.

01:47.220 --> 01:48.220
What are you
gonna do?

01:48.220 --> 01:50.730
I'm gonna sketch
the moonlit lake.

01:50.730 --> 01:51.730
Look, I know you
like to draw,

01:51.730 --> 01:53.230
but do you think this
is the right time?

01:53.230 --> 01:54.730
I'm sorry, Rich,
I'm not in the mood.

01:55.230 --> 01:56.730
I mean, that's
four cramps for Ralph

01:56.730 --> 02:00.740
and two times Potsie
fell out of the car.

02:00.740 --> 02:02.570
Well, they're very
quiet right now.

02:02.570 --> 02:05.660
Oh, Alma,
your skin is so smooth.

02:05.660 --> 02:09.660
Hands off, that's me.

02:09.660 --> 02:10.880
Smooth skin.

02:10.880 --> 02:12.050
POTSIE:
It was.

02:12.050 --> 02:13.630
Hi, Rich.

02:13.630 --> 02:14.630
Ow, Pots!

02:14.630 --> 02:15.640
Oh, sorry, Ralph.

02:15.640 --> 02:16.970
You're always sorry.

02:16.970 --> 02:18.560
Rich, you know,
your half hour is up.

02:18.560 --> 02:20.060
Potsie, get up front.

02:20.060 --> 02:21.560
Okay, I get the next
30 minutes.

02:21.560 --> 02:23.560
Right.
Come on, Alma,
up and over.

02:24.060 --> 02:24.560
Come on.
Come on now.

02:25.060 --> 02:26.060
Let me get
the backseat alone.

02:26.060 --> 02:27.060
No more than
30 minutes now.

02:27.060 --> 02:28.060
We got the back seat alone.

02:28.060 --> 02:29.070
Come on, her foot's, her foot's

02:29.070 --> 02:32.070
in the ashtray,
Rich, come on, move over.

02:32.070 --> 02:34.070
We got the backseat.
This is much better.

02:34.070 --> 02:35.570
Okay.
Better than the wet grass.

02:35.570 --> 02:38.070
Very good.

02:38.070 --> 02:39.860
Hey.

02:44.110 --> 02:45.620
I'm really sorry
about this.

02:45.620 --> 02:47.620
Not as sorry as I am.

02:47.620 --> 02:49.120
Well, look, we'll
come up here

02:49.120 --> 02:50.620
tomorrow night by
ourselves, okay?

02:50.620 --> 02:52.120
I'd rather not, Richie.

02:52.120 --> 02:53.620
Necking's kind of childish.

02:53.620 --> 02:55.120
If you had your own place...

02:55.120 --> 02:56.130
Would that make
a difference?

02:56.130 --> 02:58.130
Sure it would.

02:58.130 --> 02:59.850
Well, you know, sometimes
my parents go...

02:59.850 --> 03:02.430
Oh, blah, you still
live with your parents?

03:02.430 --> 03:06.940
Oh, no, no,
of course not.

03:06.940 --> 03:08.940
I've got my own place.

03:08.940 --> 03:10.440
Go back to
what you were doing!

03:10.440 --> 03:12.940
Certainly.

03:12.940 --> 03:14.940
You've got
your own place?

03:14.940 --> 03:15.950
Yeah, sure.

03:15.950 --> 03:18.570
How could a high school kid
afford his own apartment?

03:18.570 --> 03:20.650
Well, it's not easy
going to school

03:20.650 --> 03:23.150
and running a mail
order business.

03:23.150 --> 03:25.660
If you have your own place,
then what are we doing out here?

03:25.660 --> 03:26.660
It's being
redecorated.

03:27.160 --> 03:28.160
Sure it is.

03:28.160 --> 03:30.160
You can see it
tomorrow if you want.

03:30.160 --> 03:31.660
Really?
Yeah.

03:31.660 --> 03:34.750
Oh, I can't wait
to see it.

03:34.750 --> 03:36.750
Neither can I.

03:39.750 --> 03:41.250
MARION:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Watch this, Howard, watch{\r}.</font></font></i>

03:41.250 --> 03:43.340
King Kong.

03:43.340 --> 03:47.340
Uh, uh, uh-uh-uh,
Tarzan!

03:47.340 --> 03:49.350
Well, what else
could it be?!

03:49.350 --> 03:52.850
It's <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The Wild Ones
with Marlon Brando{\r}.</font></font></i>

03:52.850 --> 03:55.850
I don't remember any
monkeys in <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The Wild Ones{\r}.</font></font></i>

03:55.850 --> 03:57.850
Monkeys? This is
a motorcycle, Howard.

03:57.850 --> 04:00.360
How do you get a motorcycle
from that, Marion?!

04:00.360 --> 04:03.280
This is a
motorcycle!

04:04.690 --> 04:06.700
(sighs):
Oh, Howard,

04:06.700 --> 04:09.750
playing charades isn't much fun
with two people.

04:09.750 --> 04:13.340
We're not playing, Marion,
we are practicing charades,

04:13.340 --> 04:15.840
for the championship
of the Leopard Lodge!

04:15.840 --> 04:17.839
And I do not intend
finishing last

04:17.839 --> 04:19.339
for the fourth year in a row.

04:19.339 --> 04:21.839
And do you know why
we always finish last?

04:21.839 --> 04:23.380
No, dear. Why?

04:23.380 --> 04:25.100
I'll tell you why.

04:25.100 --> 04:26.180
Two words.
Mm-hmm.

04:26.180 --> 04:27.680
One, one w---
first word.

04:27.680 --> 04:29.190
Uh, little, little.

04:29.190 --> 04:30.190
Eye!

04:30.190 --> 04:31.690
Uh, second word.

04:31.690 --> 04:33.190
Nose, smell, stink.

04:33.190 --> 04:34.190
I stink!

04:34.190 --> 04:35.690
You got it!

04:39.150 --> 04:42.150
Richard, we're
playing charades.

04:42.150 --> 04:44.150
Now, what is this?
What is this?

04:44.150 --> 04:46.040
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">The Wild Ones{\r}.</font></font></i>

04:46.040 --> 04:49.240
That's my son.

04:49.240 --> 04:50.870
Two of a kind.

04:50.870 --> 04:53.960
Tell your son
he's home late.

04:53.960 --> 04:55.960
All right, that's it!

04:55.960 --> 04:57.460
I've had it!

04:57.460 --> 05:00.470
I'm 18 years old, and I'm
still treated like a kid.

05:00.470 --> 05:01.970
Guys my age are
in the mail order business

05:01.970 --> 05:03.970
and they have
their own apartments.

05:03.970 --> 05:05.970
Oh, just forget it!

05:05.970 --> 05:07.010
Oh, calm
down, dear.

05:07.010 --> 05:08.590
Well, these are nice pictures.

05:08.590 --> 05:10.090
Oh, look, there's Lake Michigan.

05:10.090 --> 05:12.100
Look at this one,
Potsie's kissing.

05:14.230 --> 05:16.320
What's that behind
Potsie's head?

05:16.320 --> 05:18.820
Ralph's foot.

05:18.820 --> 05:20.320
Look, everybody's
having a great time.

05:20.320 --> 05:21.820
Do you notice where I am?

05:21.820 --> 05:23.820
Yeah, you're right there
next to that rock.

05:23.820 --> 05:25.830
Yeah, that's right,
me and a rock,

05:25.830 --> 05:27.740
not me and a girl,
me and a rock.

05:28.330 --> 05:30.110
I'm tired of being treated
like a kid all the time.

05:30.110 --> 05:32.700
Well, we think of you as
a man, don't we, Howard?

05:32.700 --> 05:33.700
Well, of course we do.

05:33.700 --> 05:34.950
Now, you see
there, dear?

05:34.950 --> 05:36.540
Now, why don't you
just go on up to bed,

05:36.540 --> 05:38.840
and I'll come up later
with some milk and cookies.

05:44.790 --> 05:45.880
Give me a kiss right here.

05:45.880 --> 05:47.380
That's nice, yeah.

05:47.380 --> 05:48.880
Oh, sorry, Fonz. I forgot
it's cleaning day.

05:48.880 --> 05:50.380
I'll talk to you
after school.

05:50.380 --> 05:51.380
Cunningham, get back in here.

05:51.380 --> 05:53.890
The cleaning crew
was just leaving.

05:53.890 --> 05:55.390
All right, girls.

05:55.390 --> 05:59.060
You earned your kisses
and your car fare.

05:59.060 --> 06:02.150
Boy... you got the life, Fonz.

06:02.150 --> 06:03.230
Are you kidding?

06:03.230 --> 06:04.730
Look at this dust,
look at this dust.

06:04.730 --> 06:06.230
You know,
I had a girl once, Melinda,

06:06.730 --> 06:07.730
now she really liked to clean.

06:07.730 --> 06:09.370
I mean, she knew her lint.

06:09.370 --> 06:11.820
I got something to ask you,
and it's a favor.

06:11.820 --> 06:14.410
But I'm gonna ask you right out,
no beating around the bush,

06:14.410 --> 06:17.410
just head-to-head,
man-to-man.

06:17.410 --> 06:18.380
Shoot.

06:18.380 --> 06:19.460
I lied to a girl, Fonz.

06:19.460 --> 06:21.460
I told her that I had
my own apartment, and I,

06:21.460 --> 06:23.470
I'm gonna be stuck if you don't
let me use your place.

06:23.470 --> 06:24.750
What do you say?

06:24.750 --> 06:26.340
I say that every chick in town

06:26.340 --> 06:27.250
knows I live here.

06:27.250 --> 06:28.840
This girl's new in town, Fonz.

06:28.840 --> 06:30.840
Listen to this,
she's an art student.

06:30.840 --> 06:32.840
And she used to hang out
in Greenwich Village.

06:32.840 --> 06:33.840
(chuckles)

06:33.840 --> 06:35.340
Greenwich Village, Fonz.

06:35.340 --> 06:38.060
She's wild about me, she thinks
I got sexy cheekbones.

06:38.060 --> 06:40.150
Well, never
let it be said

06:40.150 --> 06:43.650
that the Fonz stands in
the way of sexy cheekbones.

06:44.100 --> 06:46.660
All right, tiger,
it's yours.

06:46.660 --> 06:47.660
Want a slug?

06:47.660 --> 06:49.490
Oh, no thanks, Fonz.
This is great.

06:49.490 --> 06:50.580
This is gonna be perfect.

06:50.580 --> 06:52.580
See, I'm an adult now,
and I'm getting tired of

06:52.580 --> 06:54.580
six people in a car,
everything's so crowded,

06:54.580 --> 06:56.580
Ralph's foot comes sticking up
in the middle,

06:56.580 --> 06:57.830
somebody honks the horn...
Cunningham,

06:57.830 --> 06:59.420
Cunningham, Cunningham,
I understand.

06:59.420 --> 07:01.420
You're an adult now,
you want an adult evening.

07:01.420 --> 07:02.460
So pick a night.

07:02.460 --> 07:03.840
Really?
Any night.

07:03.840 --> 07:04.920
Tonight.
Forget it.

07:06.930 --> 07:08.380
I-I need my rest.

07:08.380 --> 07:09.460
On Saturday night?

07:09.460 --> 07:11.050
Yeah, I like to stay home

07:11.050 --> 07:12.050
on amateur night.

07:12.050 --> 07:15.300
Fonz, I set the date
for tonight.

07:15.300 --> 07:17.390
Yeah, but I am exhausted.

07:17.390 --> 07:19.610
Yesterday, I fell asleep
on piston rings.

07:19.610 --> 07:22.190
Look, I don't even need
a whole night, Fonz.

07:22.190 --> 07:24.690
I'm just asking for half
a night, just till 12:00, huh?

07:24.690 --> 07:26.200
What do you say
about that?

07:26.200 --> 07:28.700
I say, why am I such
a sweetheart of a guy?

07:28.700 --> 07:30.820
Oh, thanks, Fonz.

07:30.820 --> 07:31.900
That's all right.

07:31.900 --> 07:33.400
Now, I bet you want me
to help you

07:33.400 --> 07:34.870
once, uh, once the girl
gets in here, right?

07:34.870 --> 07:35.960
I don't know.

07:35.960 --> 07:37.410
I'm pretty good in a car.

07:37.410 --> 07:38.990
(laughing)

07:41.490 --> 07:43.000
Oh, so cute, "in a car."

07:43.000 --> 07:44.500
This is different.
Sit down.

07:46.830 --> 07:47.920
Take this down,
Cunningham.

07:47.920 --> 07:49.250
Yeah, sure.

07:49.250 --> 07:50.340
All right.

07:50.340 --> 07:52.840
The Fonz will now recite

07:52.840 --> 07:55.760
on H.W.W.,
How to Win Women.

07:57.810 --> 08:00.400
Phase one.

08:00.400 --> 08:02.900
Your basic music,
a little poetry,

08:02.900 --> 08:04.180
you share an arepitif with her.

08:06.320 --> 08:07.900
Phase two.

08:07.900 --> 08:10.410
Anything that she likes,
you like.

08:10.410 --> 08:12.530
Anything she hates, hate.

08:12.530 --> 08:15.190
Well, what if she likes
something that's stupid?

08:15.190 --> 08:18.830
Richard, do you want to win
a debate or win a girl?

08:18.830 --> 08:20.920
Win a girl.

08:20.920 --> 08:22.030
All right.

08:22.030 --> 08:23.620
Phase three.

08:23.620 --> 08:25.920
You drop a couple of hints
that you might be willing.

08:25.920 --> 08:27.290
Willing to what?

08:29.590 --> 08:31.010
Phase four.

08:31.010 --> 08:32.630
Oh.

08:32.630 --> 08:34.710
I got to go to work,
Cunningham.

08:34.710 --> 08:35.679
Oh, uh, Fonz?

08:35.679 --> 08:38.720
Uh, how long should it take
to-to get to phase four?

08:38.720 --> 08:41.390
Well, I'd give yourself,
three to five minutes.

08:41.390 --> 08:43.470
Wait a minute.

08:43.970 --> 08:46.280
Hey, you-you do all
this in five minutes?

08:46.280 --> 08:47.860
Oh, no, no,
the first three are for you,

08:47.860 --> 08:49.860
I move right to phase four.
Whoa!

08:57.040 --> 08:58.620
Why don't you
get some sleep?

09:03.130 --> 09:04.130
You all
right, Fonz?

09:04.130 --> 09:06.130
Cunningham, I am not
gonna make it.

09:06.630 --> 09:08.920
These eyes will not
stay open till 12:00.

09:08.920 --> 09:10.500
Oh, sure they can, Fonz.

09:10.500 --> 09:12.080
You're a sweetheart of a guy.

09:12.080 --> 09:14.670
I am a beat sweetheart.

09:14.670 --> 09:17.170
Look, I understand
you want an adult evening.

09:17.170 --> 09:19.180
Pick any other night.

09:19.180 --> 09:21.180
I'll give you the pad,
I'll give you the champagne,

09:21.180 --> 09:23.260
I will supply the adult.

09:23.260 --> 09:25.350
I've got
the adult.

09:25.350 --> 09:28.350
Look, Fonz, all you have to
do is stay awake until 12:00!

09:28.350 --> 09:31.350
Richard, yelling
hurts my feelings.

09:31.350 --> 09:33.360
You're right,
you're right.

09:33.360 --> 09:36.360
I got to stay calm and
just think of a plan.

09:36.360 --> 09:37.860
I got it.
I got it.

09:37.860 --> 09:39.860
I got a
great idea.

09:39.860 --> 09:41.860
JOANIE:
Oh!
Mind your
own business.

09:41.860 --> 09:44.370
Fonz, my parents
are leaving.

09:44.370 --> 09:45.670
You can stay
in my room.

09:45.670 --> 09:46.750
No, I don't think so.

09:46.750 --> 09:49.340
I'm not very comfortable
under a Roy Rogers blanket.

09:49.340 --> 09:52.930
Oh, I got rid of that
a long time ago.

09:52.930 --> 09:54.930
Fonz, we couldn't ask
for a better night.

09:54.930 --> 09:56.930
My parents are going to
the movies with Alfred.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.430
Look, you can
sleep in my room.

09:58.430 --> 09:59.930
We'll switch
in the morning.

09:59.930 --> 10:01.430
I'll come in there
and wake you up.

10:01.430 --> 10:02.720
Nobody will
ever know.

10:02.720 --> 10:03.800
What about Joanie?

10:04.300 --> 10:04.800
Joanie's easy.

10:05.300 --> 10:06.520
(whispering)

10:06.520 --> 10:08.110
(knocking)
Joanie, don't bother
us right now!

10:08.110 --> 10:11.110
Hey, hey, hey, I think
that's the front door.

10:11.110 --> 10:13.450
What would he
do without me?

10:13.450 --> 10:15.530
Oh, come on in,
Alfred.

10:15.530 --> 10:16.530
Hi, Richie.
How are you?

10:16.530 --> 10:18.400
This is Maria.

10:18.400 --> 10:19.900
Oh, pleasant
meeting you, Maria.

10:19.900 --> 10:22.490
She doesn't understand
any English; just smile.

10:22.490 --> 10:24.990
She's from Salerno.

10:24.990 --> 10:26.490
This is Fonzie.

10:26.490 --> 10:27.990
Fonzie, this is Maria.

10:27.990 --> 10:29.500
She doesn't speak
any English; just smile.

10:31.800 --> 10:33.380
And this is...
I know,
I know.

10:33.380 --> 10:36.090
She doesn't speak any
English; I was smiling.

10:36.090 --> 10:38.000
ALFRED:
Oh, don't-
don't-don't,

10:38.000 --> 10:39.590
don't touch, no, no.

10:39.590 --> 10:42.090
That's a Leopard Lodge hat.

10:42.590 --> 10:44.090
See? Look.

10:46.600 --> 10:48.600
Leopard-o Lodge-o.

10:48.600 --> 10:49.820
Leopard...
(growls)

10:49.820 --> 10:51.900
Ah, ah, ah, Alfred.

10:51.900 --> 10:52.900
Take the hat off.

10:53.400 --> 10:55.400
You're not a Lodge member yet,
you got to earn that.

10:55.400 --> 10:58.410
Oh. You know
how bad I want it.

10:58.410 --> 10:59.910
Oh.
How do you do,
how do you do?

10:59.910 --> 11:01.410
We better hurry up
or we're gonna

11:01.410 --> 11:02.410
miss the beginning
of the movie.

11:02.410 --> 11:04.410
I'm Marion.
Oh, what a lovely suit.

11:04.410 --> 11:06.420
Children, we'll be
back in a minute.

11:06.420 --> 11:08.420
Uh, I got this at
Murray's Department Store.

11:08.420 --> 11:11.670
Maybe we'll go shopping
together sometime.

11:11.670 --> 11:15.420
Marion's talking to a girl who
doesn't understand any English.

11:15.420 --> 11:16.510
Don't worry about it.

11:16.510 --> 11:18.460
She won't find it out
for at least an hour.

11:20.600 --> 11:23.300
Well, I'm really tired.

11:23.300 --> 11:24.850
I think I'm just
gonna go on

11:24.850 --> 11:26.440
up to my room
and go to bed.

11:26.440 --> 11:27.440
Oh, yeah,
me, too.

11:27.440 --> 11:31.890
Man, I-I hope I make it
up all those steps.

11:31.890 --> 11:33.890
Good night, Shortcake.

11:36.950 --> 11:37.950
I don't believe it.

11:37.950 --> 11:39.950
I lead the most exciting life
around here,

11:39.950 --> 11:41.950
and I'm doing the dishes.

11:44.950 --> 11:45.960
(whispers):
Here's pajamas.
Hey, I don't
wear...

11:46.460 --> 11:47.460
My mother...
I will, Richie.

11:47.460 --> 11:48.410
Right.

11:49.880 --> 11:51.380
Richie, is that you?

11:51.380 --> 11:53.460
Uh...

11:53.460 --> 11:55.460
(imitating Richie):
Oh, golly, oh, gee.

11:57.970 --> 11:59.470
Yeah, it's me.

11:59.470 --> 12:01.800
Good night.
Uh, don't let the bedbugs bite.

12:01.800 --> 12:05.340
I must be getting tired;
he sounds just like <i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Howdy Doody{\r}.</font></font></i>

