12:15.350 --> 12:19.860
RICHIE (singing):
♪ I found my thrill ♪

12:20.360 --> 12:23.280
♪ On Blueberry Hill. ♪

12:23.280 --> 12:25.830
Well, this is it:
pad, sweet pad.

12:27.330 --> 12:29.330
Yeah, this is where
it all happens.

12:29.330 --> 12:31.830
Oh, Richie, this is cute.

12:31.830 --> 12:33.340
And cozy.

12:33.340 --> 12:34.340
You really like it?

12:34.340 --> 12:35.620
Oh, I sure do.

12:35.620 --> 12:37.620
Have you lived here long?

12:37.620 --> 12:38.710
Uh, no, I haven't--

12:38.710 --> 12:40.710
well, yeah,
I've lived here...

12:40.710 --> 12:42.210
Depends on what you think
long is, about a year...

12:42.210 --> 12:44.130
Yeah, way long,
long time.

12:44.130 --> 12:47.300
Well, who lives in the
main house, downstairs?

12:47.300 --> 12:49.390
Oh, those are my landlords.

12:49.890 --> 12:52.390
Oh, nice, old couple.

12:52.390 --> 12:54.390
Howard and Marion Cunning...

12:54.390 --> 12:57.390
Con, uh, Constantine.

12:57.390 --> 12:58.690
They're Greek.
Oh...

13:00.030 --> 13:02.030
"Greek"?

13:02.980 --> 13:05.530
Hey, who are all
these girls?

13:05.530 --> 13:08.040
Oh, they're just
acquaintances of mine.

13:08.040 --> 13:10.040
Well, why do they
all say, "To Fonzie"?

13:10.040 --> 13:12.040
No, no, no--
that's Funzie.

13:12.040 --> 13:13.040
I'm a fun guy,
so they call me

13:13.040 --> 13:15.540
Funzie Cunningham.
Oh.

13:15.540 --> 13:17.050
Listen, why don't
you sit down?

13:17.050 --> 13:18.910
Sit down and relax.
Okay.

13:18.910 --> 13:21.500
Uh, would you like
some music?

13:21.500 --> 13:24.000
Poetry?

13:24.000 --> 13:25.500
Share an aperitif?

13:25.500 --> 13:28.010
(both laugh)

13:28.010 --> 13:30.510
Oh, you're so
funny, Richie.

13:30.510 --> 13:31.510
Yeah, fun.

13:31.510 --> 13:32.850
(phone rings)

13:32.850 --> 13:33.930
Oh, I'll get it.
No, no, no.

13:33.930 --> 13:35.930
I'll get it, I'll get it.
This is my pad.

13:37.930 --> 13:39.940
Hello?

13:39.940 --> 13:41.940
He's not here right now.

13:41.940 --> 13:44.440
Well, listen, I'm very
busy right now,

13:44.440 --> 13:45.940
and you're just going to
have to wait your turn

13:45.940 --> 13:48.440
like everybody else.

13:48.440 --> 13:50.950
These people, they
won't leave me alone.

13:50.950 --> 13:52.700
I can see that.
Yeah.

13:52.700 --> 13:54.280
(sighs)

13:54.280 --> 13:56.250
Can I take off your sweater?
Huh?

13:56.250 --> 13:58.290
Oh, I mean, you can
leave it on if you want,

13:58.290 --> 13:59.790
but I thought you
might be a little warm.

13:59.790 --> 14:01.790
Oh, sure, sure.
Yeah.

14:01.790 --> 14:02.790
Hey, Richie.

14:02.790 --> 14:04.790
Yeah?
May I use your bathroom?

14:04.790 --> 14:06.300
Oh sure, I got one
of those, too.

14:08.050 --> 14:09.130
Oh, Richie, I like this place.

14:09.130 --> 14:11.130
I mean, I love
what you've done to it.

14:11.130 --> 14:13.140
I feel comfortable
and relaxed

14:13.140 --> 14:15.140
just like a Greenwich Village
hideaway.

14:15.140 --> 14:17.640
I can just let my hair down

14:17.640 --> 14:19.480
and be myself.

14:19.480 --> 14:21.560
Oh, let your hair down.

14:23.060 --> 14:25.060
Well, be back in a flash.

14:25.060 --> 14:27.950
All right, see you soon.
Okay.

14:27.950 --> 14:29.540
Flash.

14:29.540 --> 14:31.540
Oh.

14:31.540 --> 14:35.040
(singing):
♪ I found my thrill ♪

14:35.040 --> 14:37.990
♪ On Blueberry Hill. ♪

14:37.990 --> 14:40.550
CINDY:
Now, isn't this better
than a, than a car?

14:40.550 --> 14:43.550
(singsong):
You better believe it.

14:43.550 --> 14:45.050
In privacy.
(humming)

14:45.050 --> 14:47.050
Nobody trying to kick you.

14:47.050 --> 14:49.560
You can do anything
you feel like doing.

14:50.560 --> 14:52.560
You know, Richie,
some guys think

14:52.560 --> 14:55.060
that just because you go
to their apartment,

14:55.060 --> 14:57.430
they think they can
just take advantage of you.

14:57.430 --> 14:59.010
(humming stops)

14:59.010 --> 15:00.520
Take advantage of who?

15:00.520 --> 15:03.520
Well, I know you wouldn't
take advantage of me.

15:03.520 --> 15:04.820
(groans)

15:04.820 --> 15:07.410
(singing):
♪ I found my thrill ♪

15:07.410 --> 15:09.410
♪ On Blueberry Hill ♪

15:09.410 --> 15:11.910
♪ I'm in big trouble. ♪

15:11.910 --> 15:13.910
(humming)

15:17.920 --> 15:19.670
Well? Did you miss me?

15:19.670 --> 15:20.750
You bet.

15:22.250 --> 15:24.670
Richie, why don't
you take your tie off?

15:24.670 --> 15:27.260
Oh, you want to hear me sing
while I take my tie off?

15:27.260 --> 15:30.760
♪ I found my thrill... ♪
No, no.

15:30.760 --> 15:32.260
Take your shirt off, too.

15:32.770 --> 15:34.270
Here let me help you.

15:34.270 --> 15:36.270
Why do you want
to take off my shirt?

15:38.770 --> 15:40.270
Because I've already
sketched you

15:40.770 --> 15:41.770
in a tie and a shirt.

15:41.770 --> 15:45.280
Now I need you in a
more relaxed look.

15:46.780 --> 15:49.280
Gosh, oh, gee.

15:49.280 --> 15:51.280
I'm just another
model to you.

15:51.780 --> 15:53.290
I might as well
be a bowl of fruit.

15:55.790 --> 15:57.790
Oh Richie, no.

15:57.790 --> 16:00.240
No. Hey...

16:00.790 --> 16:01.990
I really like you.

16:01.990 --> 16:04.080
Yeah?
Uh-huh.

16:04.080 --> 16:05.580
Phase four.

16:10.170 --> 16:11.670
MARION:
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">Look, Joanie did the dishes{\r}.</font></font></i>

16:12.140 --> 16:14.090
<i><font size="24"><font face="Arial">We have such nice children{\r}.</font></font></i>

16:14.090 --> 16:16.180
I'm glad Richie got
to bed early tonight.

16:16.680 --> 16:18.180
He's a good boy.

16:18.180 --> 16:20.180
Sure is.

16:20.180 --> 16:21.680
That's why I trust him.

16:21.680 --> 16:23.680
As a matter of fact,
he's been home all evening.

16:23.680 --> 16:24.680
What makes you say that?

16:24.680 --> 16:26.190
I felt the hood of his car.

16:26.190 --> 16:27.190
It wasn't even warm.

16:27.690 --> 16:29.190
I thought you
trusted him.

16:29.190 --> 16:30.190
I do trust him.

16:30.190 --> 16:32.190
I was just checking
up on him, that's all.

16:33.690 --> 16:36.500
You know, Al's girlfriend
is a lovely person.
Mmm...

16:36.500 --> 16:39.280
It took me an hour to realize
she didn't understand English.

16:39.280 --> 16:41.280
(doorbell rings)

16:41.280 --> 16:44.370
She's terrible at charades.

16:44.370 --> 16:47.870
I wonder who it could be
at this late hour.

16:47.870 --> 16:49.010
Mrs. Cunningham?

16:49.010 --> 16:50.090
Yes.

16:50.090 --> 16:52.090
I'm Chief Petty
Officer Kendall,

16:52.090 --> 16:53.100
Cindy's father.

16:53.100 --> 16:55.100
We didn't want to rat
on Richie, he forced us.

16:55.100 --> 16:56.600
He pulled us
right out of Arnold's.

16:56.600 --> 16:57.970
We thought we
were drafted.

16:57.970 --> 17:00.050
How do you do?

17:00.050 --> 17:01.050
I'm Mr. Cunningham.

17:01.050 --> 17:03.560
Uh, would you mind telling me
what's going on here?

17:04.060 --> 17:05.109
Sir.

17:05.109 --> 17:05.970
Chief.
Oh.

17:05.970 --> 17:07.560
Excuse me, ma'am.

17:08.060 --> 17:09.560
Your son is out
with my daughter.

17:10.030 --> 17:12.060
She was supposed
to be home at 2300.

17:12.060 --> 17:15.319
It's now 2400 and I have
to be on duty at 0100.

17:15.319 --> 17:17.900
Why is he talking
in numbers?

17:20.410 --> 17:22.410
Military talk, Marion.

17:22.410 --> 17:23.540
I'll explain it later.

17:23.540 --> 17:25.160
Oh, you were in the service?

17:25.160 --> 17:27.500
I was in the Army.
I was a cook.

17:27.500 --> 17:30.420
Well, cooks always do eat better
than anybody else.

17:30.420 --> 17:32.500
Relax, Howard.

17:32.500 --> 17:33.920
May I take your hat?

17:36.840 --> 17:37.840
Okay, I'm bald.

17:37.840 --> 17:39.560
Now, where's my daughter?

17:39.560 --> 17:42.640
Well, she isn't
with Richie.

17:42.640 --> 17:45.650
He's upstairs all rolled up
in a cute little ball.

17:45.650 --> 17:47.980
He's so cute
when he sleeps.

17:47.980 --> 17:50.570
Well, your cute son, Richie,

17:50.570 --> 17:53.610
picked up my daughter tonight
at 1900 hours.

17:53.610 --> 17:56.440
Well, maybe she's out
with a different Richard.

17:56.440 --> 17:58.530
Well, he's a redheaded kid
with freckles,

17:58.530 --> 17:59.530
and he's very polite.

17:59.530 --> 18:01.410
That's him.
That's him.
Aha!

18:01.410 --> 18:02.920
Marion,

18:02.920 --> 18:06.000
you go on upstairs
and check on Richie,

18:06.000 --> 18:08.500
but if he's still
sleeping don't wake him.

18:09.510 --> 18:10.960
Uh, won't you
sit down, Chief?

18:10.960 --> 18:13.510
Well, I hate to bother you
about all of this,

18:13.510 --> 18:15.590
but I just transferred
into this area.

18:15.590 --> 18:16.680
Cindy's a Navy brat.

18:17.180 --> 18:18.680
Now, I know
your son may be okay,

18:18.680 --> 18:21.630
but, well, my daughter
is kind of wild.

18:21.630 --> 18:22.720
"Wild"?

18:22.720 --> 18:23.720
Does she have a sister?

18:26.470 --> 18:28.560
All right, that's enough.

18:28.560 --> 18:29.560
You guys, home.

18:29.560 --> 18:31.530
(Ralph and Potsie protest)
Come on, come on...

18:31.530 --> 18:34.060
All right, attention!

18:34.060 --> 18:36.530
Right face!
Forward march.

18:36.530 --> 18:39.070
Hup, two, three,
four, hup!

18:39.070 --> 18:41.570
Howie?
Hup-two,
hup-two, hup-two!

18:48.910 --> 18:52.210
Now, that's the way
to handle those boys.
Thanks.

18:52.210 --> 18:54.750
FONZIE (laughing):
Hey, hey...

18:58.800 --> 18:59.810
What was that?

18:59.810 --> 19:03.260
I am afraid to ask.

19:09.260 --> 19:11.770
That's not the
redheaded kid.

19:11.770 --> 19:13.270
Well, it must have
been some movie.

19:13.270 --> 19:15.270
You brought home
the usher.

19:20.690 --> 19:22.780
Fonzie, will you please

19:22.780 --> 19:24.500
tell me what
you're doing here?

19:24.500 --> 19:26.110
Amnesia?

19:26.110 --> 19:27.700
No.

19:27.700 --> 19:29.670
Sleepwalking?
Unh-uh.

19:29.670 --> 19:31.000
I'm open to suggestions.

19:31.000 --> 19:33.090
Come on, Fonzie!

19:33.090 --> 19:35.010
This is serious.
Now, where's Richie?

19:35.010 --> 19:36.880
I don't know, could be
any number of places.

19:36.880 --> 19:38.840
Aha!
But how did you know

19:38.840 --> 19:41.350
he wouldn't be in his room?

19:41.350 --> 19:42.350
I got lucky.

19:43.850 --> 19:46.350
Uh-huh.
Don't pay any attention to him.

19:46.350 --> 19:48.350
(all talking at once)

19:52.360 --> 19:54.940
Hello.

19:55.440 --> 19:56.950
Hey, listen,
I think I know what you want.

19:56.950 --> 20:00.070
I'll go and find Richie
and Cindy for you.
You know where they are?

20:00.070 --> 20:01.650
No, no, I don't know
where they are.

20:01.650 --> 20:03.650
I have no idea,
but don't worry about it.

20:03.650 --> 20:05.650
I mean, the Fonz
is like a bloodhound.

20:05.650 --> 20:07.160
(sniffs)

20:07.160 --> 20:09.160
Maybe they're
at Inspiration Point.

20:09.160 --> 20:11.160
Uh-huh.

20:12.660 --> 20:15.160
Well, Fonzie
is a very nice boy

20:15.160 --> 20:16.670
and if he says
he will find them,

20:16.670 --> 20:18.470
I'm just sure that he will.

20:18.470 --> 20:20.550
So why don't we just
sit down and relax?

20:20.550 --> 20:22.550
Do you have a tattoo?
Marion!

20:24.310 --> 20:26.890
Well, I guess it's
time to take a break.

20:26.890 --> 20:29.900
Yeah. I like it
like that.

20:29.900 --> 20:32.400
Draw a picture,
take a little break.

20:33.900 --> 20:35.930
Draw a picture,
take a little break.

20:35.930 --> 20:39.490
Hey, Cunningham, you're doing
real great on phase four.

20:39.490 --> 20:41.490
Did I ever describe
phase five to you?

20:41.490 --> 20:43.330
What's phase five?
Run for your life.

20:43.330 --> 20:44.580
The chick's father's
coming up the stairs.

20:44.580 --> 20:45.660
My father?
He'll kill me!

20:45.660 --> 20:47.160
All right, all
right, just cool it.

20:47.160 --> 20:48.160
Cool it, cool it, cool it.

20:48.660 --> 20:49.670
Get dressed.
Right.

20:49.670 --> 20:51.670
Where is your coat?
My coat's
right over...

20:51.670 --> 20:53.170
It's in the bed!
That's my boy!

20:53.170 --> 20:54.170
(indistinct chatter)

20:54.170 --> 20:55.670
My father's gonna kill us.

20:55.670 --> 20:57.670
All right, all right,
just take it easy.

20:57.670 --> 20:59.680
Just take it easy,
nice and cool.

20:59.680 --> 21:02.180
Get out of here before
they figure this out.

21:02.180 --> 21:03.260
We figured
it out.

21:03.260 --> 21:04.760
What is...?

21:04.760 --> 21:06.520
But we didn't
figure on this!

21:07.880 --> 21:09.470
What is
going on?

21:09.470 --> 21:10.970
I know what's going on.

21:10.970 --> 21:11.890
I'm a sailor.

21:13.770 --> 21:15.860
Look, Kendall,
they're just children.

21:15.860 --> 21:18.360
I'm sure there's a perfectly
logical explanation for this.

21:18.360 --> 21:20.860
An Army cook is going
to tell me about life?

21:20.860 --> 21:22.360
(Howard mutters)

21:22.360 --> 21:23.370
Joanie, go
to your room!

21:23.370 --> 21:25.370
What are you
yelling at me for?

21:25.370 --> 21:27.790
I was the only one
in the right bed.

21:27.790 --> 21:28.870
(indistinct chatter)

21:28.870 --> 21:30.870
Joanie, will you get out
of here?

21:30.870 --> 21:33.880
(all talking at once)

21:33.880 --> 21:36.880
All right, all right, time out!

21:36.880 --> 21:38.130
Hold it!

21:38.130 --> 21:39.210
(silence)

21:39.210 --> 21:40.720
FONZIE:
Now, listen,

21:40.720 --> 21:43.220
I think you're all
very charming, but the thing is,

21:43.220 --> 21:46.810
this is what you might call
a middle class problem, you see?

21:46.810 --> 21:48.810
And I can't be of any help

21:48.810 --> 21:51.310
since I'm in a class
all by myself.

21:51.310 --> 21:53.810
So why don't you just
take this on down

21:53.810 --> 21:55.480
to your middle class
living room?

21:55.480 --> 21:57.570
He's right. Come on,
let's all go downstairs.

21:57.570 --> 21:58.770
We'll settle it there.

21:58.770 --> 22:00.850
Come on.
Richard?

22:02.850 --> 22:04.360
Oh, uh,

22:04.360 --> 22:05.520
Cunningham?

22:05.520 --> 22:07.160
Good luck.
HOWARD:
Richard,

22:07.160 --> 22:08.240
we're waiting!

22:08.240 --> 22:11.160
Phase six--
explaining to my father.

22:18.290 --> 22:20.290
Hey, Jim, you were here.

22:20.290 --> 22:22.290
Just answer me one question.

22:22.290 --> 22:24.790
How'd he get the coat
in the bed?

22:30.720 --> 22:31.720
Well?

22:31.720 --> 22:33.720
Okay, okay, I'll admit

22:33.720 --> 22:35.720
these sketches
must have taken a lot of time,

22:35.720 --> 22:37.860
but who knows
what else they did?

22:37.860 --> 22:40.940
Listen, Kendall,
I know my son,
and if he says

22:40.940 --> 22:43.730
all they did was draw
sketches, then I believe him.

22:43.730 --> 22:46.620
KENDALL:
Well,

22:46.620 --> 22:47.700
maybe you're right.

22:47.700 --> 22:49.700
Cindy, let's go home.

22:49.700 --> 22:52.200
We can talk about this
tomorrow at 0600.

22:52.200 --> 22:54.210
That's 6:00 a.m.

22:54.210 --> 22:55.210
Bye, Richie.

22:55.210 --> 22:58.210
I hope I get to sketch
you again sometime.

22:58.210 --> 23:02.210
Yeah, sure, we'll draw a little,
take a little break, yeah.

23:02.210 --> 23:05.300
Okay, wait
in the jeep, sailor.

23:05.300 --> 23:06.800
Uh... Cindy.

23:06.800 --> 23:08.800
Sorry, honey.

23:08.800 --> 23:10.810
You know, I just
don't understand it.

23:10.810 --> 23:14.310
I handle 1,700 raw recruits,
and they tow the line.

23:14.810 --> 23:17.430
With my own daughter,
I got no communication.

23:17.430 --> 23:19.510
She's not
Navy, Kendall.

23:19.510 --> 23:21.020
She's your daughter.

23:21.020 --> 23:23.020
Why don't you try
talking to her?

23:23.020 --> 23:25.100
But I'm a busy man.
I don't have the time.

23:25.100 --> 23:27.190
Well, you found enough
time to have her.

23:27.190 --> 23:29.110
Can't you find some
time to spend with her?

23:32.080 --> 23:34.080
Thanks. I'll try.

23:34.080 --> 23:36.580
You know, I don't know why
she never sketches me.

23:36.580 --> 23:37.580
I mean, I'm easy.

23:37.580 --> 23:40.040
It isn't as if
you have to draw hair.

23:40.040 --> 23:41.540
I have a very simple face.

23:46.510 --> 23:48.510
You know, Dad,
I really appreciate

23:48.510 --> 23:50.430
the way you backed me up.

23:50.430 --> 23:52.300
Oh.
You really
must trust me.

23:52.300 --> 23:53.880
Well, of course I trust you.

23:53.880 --> 23:55.380
Yeah.

23:55.380 --> 23:57.270
Richie, what really
happened, huh?

24:12.820 --> 24:14.400
Well, Dad,
it's-it's getting a little late.

24:14.400 --> 24:16.400
You're not going
to lecture me tonight, are you?

24:16.400 --> 24:18.410
No, I'm not going to
give you a lecture.

24:18.410 --> 24:20.910
Look, Richie, I know
you're getting older,

24:20.910 --> 24:24.410
and you want to be an adult
and do things that adults do.

24:24.910 --> 24:25.910
Yeah, I sure do.

24:25.910 --> 24:28.420
Well, I'm not going
to stop you.

24:28.420 --> 24:30.420
I couldn't if
I wanted to.

24:30.420 --> 24:32.920
But just remember, if
you ever need my help,

24:32.920 --> 24:34.810
you can always
come to me.

24:34.810 --> 24:38.430
I may yell at you a little
bit, but I'll help you.

24:38.430 --> 24:39.510
Thanks, Dad.
Mm.

24:39.510 --> 24:41.010
Do you think next week

24:41.010 --> 24:43.180
you could help me look
for an apartment?

24:43.180 --> 24:44.850
What?!

24:44.850 --> 24:46.430
Upstairs!
Oh...

24:46.430 --> 24:47.940
Hut, two, three,
four, come on.

24:47.940 --> 24:49.440
All right...
Hut, two,
hut, two.

